title: My Fair Lady
overview: Snobbish phonetics Professor Henry Higgins agrees to a wager that he can make flower girl Eliza Doolittle presentable in high society.

title: Veer-Zaara
overview: Veer-Zaara is a saga of love, separation, courage and sacrifice. A love story that is an inspiration and will remain a legend forever.

title: Taare Zameen Par
overview: An eight-year-old boy is thought to be a lazy trouble-maker, until the new art teacher has the patience and compassion to discover the real problem behind his struggles in school.

title: Babam ve Oglum
overview: The family of a left-wing journalist is torn apart after the military coup of Turkey in 1980.

title: Wonder
overview: Based on the New York Times bestseller, this movie tells the incredibly inspiring and heartwarming story of August Pullman, a boy with facial differences who enters the fifth grade, attending a mainstream elementary school for the first time.

title: Rebel Without a Cause
overview: A rebellious young man with a troubled past comes to a new town, finding friends and enemies.

title: Ace in the Hole
overview: A frustrated former big-city journalist now stuck working for an Albuquerque newspaper exploits a story about a man trapped in a cave to rekindle his career, but the situation quickly escalates into an out-of-control circus.

title: Manchester by the Sea
overview: A depressed uncle is asked to take care of his teenage nephew after the boy's father dies.

title: Anand
overview: The story of a terminally ill man who wishes to live life to the fullest before the inevitable occurs, as told by his best friend.

title: Rockstar
overview: Janardhan Jakhar chases his dreams of becoming a big Rock star, during which he falls in love with Heer.

title: All That Jazz
overview: Director/choreographer Bob Fosse tells his own life story as he details the sordid career of Joe Gideon, a womanizing, drug-using dancer.

title: The Grapes of Wrath
overview: A poor Midwest family is forced off their land. They travel to California, suffering the misfortunes of the homeless in the Great Depression.

title: A Little Princess
overview: A young girl is relegated to servitude at a boarding school when her father goes missing and is presumed dead.

title: Cat on a Hot Tin Roof
overview: Brick is an alcoholic ex-football player who drinks his days away and resists the affections of his wife. A reunion with his terminal father jogs a host of memories and revelations for both father and son.

title: Dancer in the Dark
overview: An East European girl travels to the United States with her young son, expecting it to be like a Hollywood film.

title: Bacheha-Ye aseman
overview: After a boy loses his sister's pair of shoes, he goes on a series of adventures in order to find them. When he can't, he tries a new way to "win" a new pair.
stars: ['Mohammad Amir Naji', 'Amir Farrokh Hashemian', 'Bahare Seddiqi', 'Nafise Jafar-Mohammadi']

title: Kramer vs. Kramer
overview: Ted Kramer's wife leaves him, allowing for a lost bond to be rediscovered between Ted and his son, Billy. But a heated custody battle ensues over the divorced couple's son, deepening the wounds left by the separation.

title: The Boy in the Striped Pyjamas
overview: Through the innocent eyes of Bruno, the eight-year-old son of the commandant at a German concentration camp, a forbidden friendship with a Jewish boy on the other side of the camp fence has startling and unexpected consequences.

title: Judgment at Nuremberg
overview: In 1948, an American court in occupied Germany tries four Nazis judged for war crimes.

title: Scent of a Woman
overview: A prep school student needing money agrees to "babysit" a blind man, but the job is not at all what he anticipated.
